        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Pottsville</placeName>
                <date>July 14/64</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)"><del>Dear</del> Honorable Sir:</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">It is a long time since I<lb/> wrote to you. But <del>it was</del>
                not negligence on<lb/> my part <del>but rather</del> is to blame, but rather<lb/>
                these upsetting times. I am happy, to find in<lb/> your paper that you are still
                    grinding<add>?</add> with<lb/> a strong hand the shop Jewish religious
                conditions<lb/> in <placeName>America</placeName>. God bless you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">As far as I and my family are<lb/> concerned: Everything is
                fine.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Let me tell you something about<lb/> our own congregation because I
                know you<lb/> are interested in religious things. Our congr.<lb/> got many new
                members in the last year and<lb/> a new life came into the meetings. A regular
                        <add><date>Rosh Hodesh</date>
                    <add>?</add>
                    <date>Sabbath</date></add> service is held each <add>ר"ח ל"ג</add> and other
                holidays.<lb/> I can flatter myself that everybody is<lb/> satisfied with my service
                and I'll try to<lb/> keep it up. My speeches on the holidays<lb/> caused large
                attendances of various<lb/> denominations. Last <add>שבועות</add>
                <add><date>Shabu-oth</date></add> for the first</p>
            <p rend="Note:">“<date>Rosh Hodesh</date>
                <add>?</add>
                <date>Sabbath</date>” in the paragraph above is inserted in the left margin.</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">2</p>
            <p>time I confirmed 4 children and everybody<lb/> was highly<add>?</add> pleased.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The 8 synagogue was filled by people<lb/> of various denominations.
                Many people thanked<lb/> me and <add>I got generous presents from</add> the parents
                of the children whom I had<lb/> confirmed. I hope to be able to give you soon<lb/>
                good news again.</p>
            <p>(Please, read English on 3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> page of original)</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Another point I wish to mention<lb/> Since I came to
                    <placeName>Pottsville</placeName> I was two<lb/> times in
                    <placeName>Danville</placeName> as a <add>קדוש</add>
                <add>preacher</add> I<lb/> found this congregation in a very bad con-<lb/>dition. It
                is a herd without a leader.<lb/> The dust in the synagogue was ½ inch high<lb/>
                because it has not been used for a long<lb/> while.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Let me tell you an incident<lb/> concerning <persName>Mr.
                    Oettinger</persName> of the <placeName>Danville</placeName><lb/> Parnass. On
                    <date>Sunday July 3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi></date> he was<lb/> arrested at the
                meeting of the congregation<lb/> was put in jail and brought to
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> the next day. I <sic>dont</sic> doubt
